&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;River Neighbourhood Team – Stourport Health Centre&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 Hours per week – Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Worcestershire Community Services – Where Integrated Care works&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to be part of a great Integrated Care Partnership?  Come and join us – working in Neighbourhood Teams to support people with Nursing, Physiotherapy or Occupational Therapy support needs across the beautiful county of Worcestershire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have established 13 teams around Worcestershire from Evesham through to Malvern, Pershore, Kidderminster, Redditch, Droitwich, Bromsgrove and Tenbury.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The teams work closely with GP and social care partners to provide a wide variety of nursing and rehabilitation services to people in their own homes.  We care for people with a range of needs from the simple to complex.  We pool our collective resources to make shared decisions and plans to support people to be as independent as possible at home.  Whether you are great at giving IVs, have a passion for delivering quality end of life care or enjoy the rewards of community delivered reablement we have a role for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of our ongoing development we are currently growing these teams to provide rapid response hospital admission avoidance and are committed to a Home First philosophy of care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You give us …..enthusiasm, a commitment to working in an integrated way, clinical excellence or an ability and desire to learn the right clinical skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return…. We will give you – excellent training opportunities, full induction, ongoing supervision and mentorship.  We offer planned career pathways to help you achieve your potential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and talk to us – we offer a range of working hours …….. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in finding out more about this role please contact Louise Coley-Holland &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;louise.coley-holland@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
